      • rightMultByMatrix

        public static MatrixBlock rightMultByMatrix(List<ColGroup> colGroups,
                                            MatrixBlock that,
                                            MatrixBlock ret,
                                            int k,
                                            org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Pair<Integer,int[]> v,
                                            boolean allowOverlap)
        Right multiply by matrix. Meaning a left hand side compressed matrix is multiplied with a right hand side uncompressed matrix.
        Parameters:
        colGroups - All Column groups in the compression
        that - The right hand side matrix
        ret - The MatrixBlock to return.
        k - The parallelization degree to use.
        v - The Precalculated counts and Maximum number of tuple entries in the column groups.
        allowOverlap - Allow the multiplication to return an overlapped matrix.
        Returns:
        The Result Matrix, modified from the ret parameter.

        colGroups - The Column groups used int the multiplication
        vector - matrix block vector to multiply with
        result - matrix block result to modify in the multiplication
        k - number of threads to use
